news.title: Institutional investors infuse $637.9 million in Indian real estate in Q1 FY25
news.para: As per the data, institutional investments in the Indian real estate rose 96 per cent in April-June to USD 3.1 billion from USD 1.6 billion in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Coimbatore’s wait for final masterplan continues
news.para: Local Planning Authority (LPA) officials said they were flooded with more than 3,000 objections and suggestions for the draft masterplan.

news.title: About 199 dilapidated buildings in Nagpur facing risk of accidents
news.para: As pre-monsoon measures, the Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) conducts surveys of dilapidated buildings in the city and issues notices to vacate them.

news.title: Odisha: Court orders attachment of properties of Shri Sai Infrastructure for duping investors
news.para: The court has been set up under the Odisha Protection of Interests of Depositors (OPID) Act, the court also ordered the public auction and equitable distribution of the money among the investors, Panda said.

news.title: Innov8 starts three centres in Delhi-NCR with Rs 10 crore investment
news.para: "Delhi NCR's thriving startup ecosystem and its position as a major corporate hub make it an ideal location for our latest co-working spaces," Ritesh Malik, Founder of Innov8, said.

news.title: Eldeco and Purvanchal buys land from YEIDA for Rs 250 crore
news.para: Another Noida based developer Purvanchal projects has bought an 40,000 sq metre land for Rs 149.47 crore, both the land parcels are for group housing projects and developers are expected to build high rises on the acquired land.

news.title: Kolkata civic body won’t allow more than 10% violation in built-up area
news.para: A KMC buildings department senior official said they were struggling to demolish several newly constructed buildings across the city where an entire floor has been constructed without sanction.

news.title: Panchkula court accepts M3M promoters' bond filed under section 88 of CrPC
news.para: Earlier on February 23, 2024, Bansals appeared before the Special Court (PMLA), Panchkula, in compliance with the summons issued by the court on February 20, 2024.

news.title: Noida authority raises land allotment prices by 6% for FY25
news.para: The meeting was chaired by UP Chief Secretary and Authority Chairperson Manoj Kumar Singh and attended by Noida Authoriy CEO Lokesh M and Additional CEO Ravindra Kumar along with various board members.

news.title: Haryana cabinet approves scheme to provide affordable housing for EWS
news.para: Those having annual family income of up to Rs 1.80 lakh as per the 'Parivar Pehchan Patra' (family id) and do not own a 'pucca' house in any urban area of Haryana will be eligible for the housing scheme.

news.title: Housing crisis in Spain's cities drives rise in homelessness
news.para: The 62-year-old pensioner found he couldn't afford rental prices in the capital when he moved from Jaen in southern Spain to seek treatment for throat cancer.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's sales bookings up by 29.7% in Q1 FY25
news.para: "We had pre-sales of ~Rs 502 crores in Q1 FY25, up 29.7% on year-on-year basis," Sunteck Realty said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Supply of affordable housing dips 21% in top seven cities in Q1 FY25: Report
news.para: Of the total new supply in the June quarter, the launches of affaordable flats stood at 13,277 units, a fall of 21 per cent from 16,728 units in the same period last year.

news.title: Puravankara reports sales bookings of Rs 1,128 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The average price realisation increased to Rs 8,746 per sq ft during the first quarter of 2024-25, up 6 per cent from Rs 8,277 per sq ft in the year-ago period.

news.title: Uniform payout for landowners near Noida sector 18
news.para: The case got complicated with different batches of landowners getting different rates of compensation: Rs 340 per sq yd fixed by the Allahabad High Court.

news.title: Goa's revenue minister to not allow any development on converted land
news.para: The revenue minister said that not only he, but even the other ministers are disturbed with the land conversions in their respective constituencies.

news.title: Cement companies' earnings likely to stay weak
news.para: Demand for the primary building materials being relatively lower has further added to the pricing woes, as makers have not been able to sustain any hikes taken during the quarter.

news.title: UP-RERA directs authorities not to issue temporary occupancy certificate
news.para: Uttar Pradesh RERA has directed all the industrial and housing development authorities to give the names of the relevant towers or blocks of the project with respect to which the part-C.C. or O.C.

news.title: TA Associates leads $400 million investment in Vastu Housing Finance
news.para: Financial details of the transaction were not disclosed. People familiar with the matter said the investors bought the stake for about ₹3,340 crore ($400 million) and it valued Vastu at ₹10,000 crore.
